#Conditional statement;
so condition is becically when you do something by your program using condition

#there is somekind of condition ;
1. if 
2. if else
3. else if
4. switch 
5. ternary

**lets see how they work and how i use them

1. if statement:
  so when you have to do a condition than use if statement.
#syntex:

if (condition){
  console.log(what you wanna print)
}

so if your if condition return something ture than console.log will be print otherwise it will not print

^^ here is some example

let age = 27                          //age is a variable and its value is 27

if(age=>18){                         // here i give condition if age greter or equal to 18
    console.log("you can vote")     // condition is true now it will print
}
output;
you can vote

2.if else statement:
  so its be like another if statement but twist is now if it don't give true result you can print false result.
#syntex;
if (condition){
  console.log(if true;what you wanna print)
} esle {
  console.log(if false;what you wanna print)
}

^^ here is example
let age =15                         //age is a variable and its value is 15

if(age>=18){                          // here i give condition if age greter or equal to 18
    console.log("you can vote")       // if true than print this
} else{
    console.log("you cant vote")        // if false print this
}
output;
you cant vote

3.if ,else if , else statement:
  so when you have many condition than use it 
syntex;
if (condition1) {
  // code if condition1 is true
} else if (condition2) {
  // code if condition2 is true
} else {
  // code if none of the conditions are true
}
-you can add more condition on it













@Question solve for #condition:

1.Ask the user for their age and print:

"Child" if age < 13
"Teen" if age >= 13 and < 20
"Adult" if age >= 20
ans;
let age = Number(prompt('pls enter your age;'))

if(age<13){
    console.log("you are child");
} else if (age <= 20){              // i made a mistake on there just remove =
    console.log("you are teen");
} else{
    console.log("you are adult");
}


2.Check if a number is even or odd and print the result.
ans;
let number = Number(prompt('input a number you wanna see odd or even you dumbass'))

if(number%2===0){
    console.log('your number is even bro')
} else{
    console.log('your number is odd bro')
}

3.Take a number and check:

Print "Positive" if > 0
Print "Negative" if < 0
Print "Zero" if it’s 0
ans;

let num = Number(prompt("Pick a Number My Dear"))

if(num>0){
    console.log("Positive");
} else if (num<0){
    console.log("Negetive");
} else {
    console.log('sorry my dear you chose zero');
}



4.Ask the user to enter a month number (1-12) and print the corresponding month name using if...else if.
ans;

let month = Number(prompt("Enter a number (1-12) to see the month"));

if (month === 1) console.log("January");
else if (month === 2) console.log("February");
else if (month === 3) console.log("March");
else if (month === 4) console.log("April");
else if (month === 5) console.log("May");
else if (month === 6) console.log("June");
else if (month === 7) console.log("July");
else if (month === 8) console.log("August");
else if (month === 9) console.log("September");
else if (month === 10) console.log("October");
else if (month === 11) console.log("November");
else if (month === 12) console.log("December");
else console.log("Invalid month number");



5.Login System (Real-life logic)
Given:

username = "admin"
password = "1234"

Input values:
If both correct → "Login successful"
If username correct but password wrong → "Wrong password"
If username wrong → "Invalid user"

my ans:
let ueserName= "admin"
let password = 1234

let name = prompt('Enter your user name')
let pass= Number(prompt("Enter your password"))


if (ueserName===name && password === pass){
    console.log('welcome chif')
} else if (ueserName!==name){
    console.log("invalid username")
} else {
    console.log("wrong password")
}
#it was almost perfect by here is the right one^^

if (ueserName === name && password === pass) {
    console.log("Login successful")
} else if (ueserName === name && password !== pass) {
    console.log("Wrong password")
} else {
    console.log("Invalid user")
}


#### this is my condition project 
let weight= Number(prompt('enter your weight in kg'))
let hight = Number(prompt('enter your hight in meter'))


let a = weight/(hight*hight);

if (a >= 30){
    console.log(`obese`)
} else if (a >=25){
    console.log('overweight')
} else if (a >=18.5){
    console.log('normal')
} else  {
    console.log('under weight')
}





